msg: Display the proper URL for a deletion when prompting for the log message.
The existing code assumes that the relpaths passed to it are relative to the
repository root.  Rather, the code in delete_urls_multi_repos() groups URLs by
repository root and then condenses the URLs to find the longest possible session
parent.  This means if you issued the command:
You'll end up seeing the following in your editor:
(single_repos_delete): Rename repos_root to base_uri since we don't need the
root but rather the session parent.
(delete_urls_multi_repos): Remove repos_root variable that is no longer used,
